All Classes

Class Description
BackEnd
BackEnd is the class in which the current state of the FSM implemented through the pattern state is decided
BeginningMatchWindow
It is the waiting window before the beginning of the match.
Build
Build is an interface based on the strategy pattern for the build method
BuildAtlas
BuildAtlas implements the build strategy for Atlas
BuildDefault
BuildDefault implements the normal build strategy
BuildState
BuildState is a class part of the FSM of the controller.
BuildZeus
BuildZeus implements the build strategy for Zeus
ChallengerWindow
It is the window where the challenger can choose the gods he wants to play with.
CharonSwitchState
CharonSwitchState is the class that represents the status of the FSM in which used for the special power of Charon, the current worker exchanges his position with the opponent's position.
ChooseGodWindow
It is the window where the player can choose the god to play with, among those chosen by the challenger.
ChooseWorkerState
ChooseWorkerState is the class that represents the status of the FSM in which the current player chooses the worker to play with
ClientConnection
It represents the client itself during his match
ClientMain  
ClientMessage
It is the message sent to the server to describe the client's choices.
CLIPrinter
CLIPrinter contains the method used to print a game table
ColourFont
It contains the colours used by the CLI.
CommandLineGame
It defines the command line interface for the user and all the logic behind it.
Constraint
Constraint is the class responsible to keep trace of Hypnus and Athena.
ExistingGameWindow
It is the window where the player types a gameID ot play an existing match with friends.
FrontEnd
FrontEnd is a virtual view, which manages the turns of the match and notifies the BackEnd
Game
The class Game represents the core of the game, describing the status of the current match
GameMessage
GameMessage is the message sent by the remote view (the FrontEnd) to the controller (the BackEnd), it contains the information for an action performed in a player's turn
GameState
GameState is an interface for a state of the controller
GameWindow
It has a static GUIHandler as an attribute.
God
The God enum is the list of gods available in the game
GUIHandler
It is the interface of GUI towards and backwards network.
GUILauncher
It launches the graphical user interface
LiteGame
Class used as a message to send to the virtual view
Message
Message is an enum class for the different type of messages the server sends to the client.
MessageHandler
It is the handler of all the message coming in and out on the internet.
Mode
It contains all the possible choices a player can take to start playing.
ModeWindow
It is the window where the player can choose the way she/he wants to start a game.
Move
Move is a strategy pattern interface for the move method
MoveApollo
MoveApollo implements the move strategy for Apollo
MoveDefault
MoveDefault implements the normal move strategy
MoveMinotaur
MoveMinotaur implements the move strategy for Minotaur
MoveState
MoveState is the class that represents the state of the FSM in which the current worker execute his move
NewGameWindow
It is the window where the player chooses the number of players.
NicknameWindow
It is the window where the player can choose a nickname.
Observable<T>
Observable is an implementation of the observable object of the observer pattern
Observer<T>
Observer is an interface for the observer object of the observer pattern
OpeningMirror
It is the first class shown to the client
PlaceWorkersState
PlaceWorkerState is a class that represents the state of the FSM in which the current player places his workers
Player
Player is used to keep trace of a player in the match
PrometheusBuildState
A GameState made for Prometheus in order to make a build and then move his worker without moving up
PrometheusMoveState
A GameState which follows the PrometheusBuildState in order to make Prometheus use his power
RemovePlayerState
A GameState which performs the remove of a player from the game
SerializableLiteGame
SerializableLiteGame is a serializable version of the LiteGame class, which will be sent to the client
Server
Server is the main server class
ServerConnection
ServerConnection is responsible of the communication with a client
ServerMain  
SetPlayersState
SetPlayerState is the initial GameState, it receives the name and gods of the players and creates a game table
SettingGameMessage
It is the message used at the beginning of the game, to fix it.
Space
Space is used to describe a game table space
TableWindow
It is the window where the match is actually played.
WaitingWindow
It is the window where the player waits for other players to join the match.
WelcomeWindow
It describes every graphical object implemented in the starting window of the application.
WinState
A GameState that ends the match
Worker
Worker is used to describe a worker
